    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect initialization in nrLDPC_bnProcPc_BG2_generator_AVX512 for first CN group\n\n### Summary\nThe `nrLDPC_bnProcPc_BG2_generator_AVX512` function in the LDPC decoder contained logic errors when generating code for the first CN group (1 CN connection). This caused incorrect AVX-512 assembly to be produced for BG2 LDPC decoding, leading to corrupted decoded data.\n\nThe issue was in the first group processing where:\n1. `zmmRes0` and `zmmRes1` were never initialized with values from `zmm0` and `zmm1`\n2. Incorrect loading from `p_llrProcBuf[j]` instead of `p_bnProcBuf[j + 1]`\n3. Invalid accumulation logic for a group that should only have 1 CN\n\nUnder high throughput conditions with BG2 LDPC codes, this manifested as increased block error rates and occasional segfaults in the AVX-512 decoding path.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc_avx512/bnProcPc_gen_BG2_avx512.c`: Fixed first group processing logic to properly initialize result registers and follow correct AVX-512 pattern\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc_avx512/bnProcPc_gen_BG1_avx512.c`: Applied same correction to BG1 generator for consistency\n\n"
}